          ## What's on?

          ### Saturday Hub

          ##### Manchester Central Library

          Hosts an exploration of the lives of LGBT people throughout history, with new research by members of the public and historians. Members of the community will share their stories and experiences.

          ### Sunday Hub

          ##### People’s History Museum

          Will be hosting discussions of power and institutions, and the role of social movements in changing rights for LGBT people.
          
          ### Film 
          We are showcasing film representations of LGBT diversity, including a specific focus on German film's pioneering role in representing sex and gender diversity on the screen.
          
          ### Theatre 
          Pagelight Productions will dramatise a historic raid of a fancy dress ball in Hulme in September 1880 and show why this event made the international news.
          
          ### Academic Conference 
          The LGF hosts an academic conference 'The 2nd What is & How to DO LGBT History?', which seeks to place attitudes, experiences and identities in their historical context.
          
          ### Family Events 
          Both Saturday and Sunday feature diversity and LGBT history lessons, delivered by experienced teachers, for Key Stages 1 & 2. There will also be story time for younger children and teenagers.
